  "input": {
    "question_id": "Q2",
    "framework": "CAIQ",
    "text": "Are independent audit and assurance assessments conducted according to relevant standards at least annually?"
  },
  "outbound_response": "Yes. BNY's independent registered public accounting firm, KPMG, is engaged on an annual basis to perform the audit of the company's financial statements and to attest to the operating effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting, and KPMG complies with the auditing, quality control and independence standards and rules of the PCAOB and the SEC [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-24-051895::Item_5#0154]. The Audit Committee of the Board has direct responsibility for the selection, appointment, compensation, retention and oversight of the independent registered public accountants engaged to prepare the audit report or to perform other audit, review or attestation services, and is responsible for negotiating and approving all audit engagement fees and terms [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-24-051895::Item_5#0151]. The Audit Committee annually evaluates KPMG, including its qualifications and independence, with the assistance of a management-prepared annual assessment that considers KPMG's continued independence, its understanding of the financial services industry and of BNY's business, and the professionalism of its engagement team [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-25-046216::Item_3#0150]. The Committee also receives the written disclosures and letter from KPMG required by applicable PCAOB standards regarding auditor independence and conducts a discussion with KPMG regarding its independence [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-25-046216::Item_3#0152]. Based on these annual reviews and discussions, the Audit Committee recommends to the Board the inclusion of the audited financial statements in BNY's Annual Report [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-25-046216::Item_3#0152].",
